The budget shall be prepared to include the following categories:
Current expense fund, estimated receipts:
Revenue from local sources;
Revenue from State sources;
Revenue from federal sources;
Unliquidated surplus, the actual from the previous fiscal year and the estimated from the current fiscal year, whether accrued from revenues or expenditures; and
Revenue from all other sources with identification of the source.
Current expense fund, requested appropriations:
Administration, which means those activities associated with the general regulations, direction, and control of the county board, including:
Mid-level administration, including:
Instructional salaries, which means those activities which deal directly with teaching students, including:
Textbooks and classroom instructional supplies;
Other instructional costs;
Special education with subcategories and items budgeted in this category to be determined by the State Board with the advice of the county board;
Student personnel services;
Health services;
Student transportation;
Operation of plant and equipment;
Maintenance of plant;
Fixed charges;
Food services; and
Capital outlay.
School construction fund, estimated receipts:
Revenue from local sources;
Sale of bonds;
State General Public School Construction Loan;
Revenue from State sources;
Revenue from federal sources;
Unliquidated surplus, the actual from the previous fiscal year and the estimated for the current fiscal year, whether accrued from revenues or expenditures; and
Funds from all other sources, with identification of the source.
School Construction Fund, requested appropriations:
Land for school sites;
Buildings and the equipment that will be an integral part of a building by project;
School site improvement by project;
Remodeling by project;
Additional equipment by project;
Debt service; and
An amount that is adequate to satisfy a final court judgment that, after exhaustion of the rights of appeal, is rendered against the county board of education or any of its officers or employees.
